Daimler, BASF, K+S: German Equity Market Preview for March 11

-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-03-11T05:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/daimler-basf-k-s-german-equity-market-preview-for-march-11.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in  Germany . Stock symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are
from the previous close.  The benchmark DAX Index fell 68.71 points, or 1 percent, to
7,063.09.    Daimler AG (DAI)  : The maker of luxury cars and Rolls-
Royce Group Plc (RR/ LN) plan to resist calls to raise their
joint takeover offer for heavy-duty engine manufacturer  Tognum
AG (TGM)   even as the stock hovers above the bid price, two
people close to the companies said. Daimler fell 2.2 percent to
48.71 euros. Tognum rose 2.4 percent to 25.50 euros.  BASF AG (BAS GY): The oil exploration, production and
chemicals company plans to sell its remaining stake in potash
maker K+S AG, valued at as much as 1 billion euros ($1.4
billion) at current market prices, marking a further move away
from its commodity chemical past. BASF fell 1.1 percent to 58.73
euros.  K+S AG (SDF GY):  Europe ’s biggest potash producer’s chief
executive said that the company was ruling out bids for BASF’s
fertilizer assets. The stock fell 1.8 percent to 54.24 euros.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  